author: @nosae4385
text:
ok here's my take:

Taeyong was the kid from The Origin. He was the first to discover about this interconnected dreams, also known as NCT, and WinWin was his first contact. And then we got the 2nd vid which obviously revealed what happened, The synchronization of dreams. There. Taeyong began to dream and connect other members' dreams. And then on the 3rd vid, we have WinWin dancing in a wavy motion which somehow hint of the 3rd unit, WayV, which represents Vision of the group or seeing events happening while dreaming. NCT Dream is like their FIRST STATION, it's like phase 1, it's a member's dreaming stage where they are crafting this dream like power and when successful, they can move to the next stage or new units (which was NCT Dream's original concept but NCT Dream became a fixed unit). And of course 127, which is their main location and where it all started. Now we are here in 2021 and it looks like Sungchan and Shotaro will be part of something bigger as well, maybe a new unit coming soon.

Conclusion: so I think 127 is the main location, Dream is where they manifest the power, WayV as their Vision and NCT as the best kpop group to ever exist,

author: @WeAreAllMadeOfTubes
text:
I love these NCT teasers (like 2018's NCTmentary and 2020's YearParty/Ether). And again, it's tying into SM's grand concept of Revival/Restoration/Return, going back to the beginning, to the past (MV remastering project, NCT's debut song/teaser, "Hello Future") in order to go forward.

Worlds are colliding. Batons are getting passed. One chapter ends (NCT 2021 in graduation sashes?) but a new chapter begins (Sungchan and Shotaro, a new NCT group). It's NCT: Endgame! It's the Great Reset! It's Dave Bowman going through the stargate in "2001: A Space Odyssey" (what "Make A Wish" (Birthday Song) was about)!

SO excited.

text: So first off I love this, second I think I actually might understand what's going on! To me this reads as Taeyong finding Sungchan and Shotaro and then introducing them to the beginning of NCT, and then synchronizing them into the dream NCT all share. Taeyong as the leader would probably be the first person to do all that. He even said, "this time, two", implying he's done this before. text: I'm gonna say SM is truly genius, they had wide and long-term plan for NCT since then and for the future, and they truly nailed it with the help of nct members as a whole. NCT is the basis for "New Culture Technology" introduced by SM, and then they created Neo Culture Technology (NCT) as the pillar for that. Imagine the burden of nct members to carry out the first system ever to happen in kpop world, with limitless members and keep on growing. Not to say the more burden and pressure the newer members is since they will debut in an experienced group under the name of nct, instead of debuting in a whole different new group. And imagine how good and skilled they have to be, to be debuted under nct where when they perform with nct members, you'll get that nct feels in them (if u know what i mean). I'll always be here supporting each one of them till the end. They set the standard. Periodt.

author: @Kim-tz6ui
text:
Penjelasan video
bagi yang belum paham... video ini membawa kita ke NCTmentary selama Era Empati. pada dasarnya NCT didasarkan pada gagasan bahwa para anggota terhubung melalui berbagai mimpi yang sama. NCTmentary berbicara tentang para anggota yang berbagi gelombang otak yang sama dan menghubungkan harapan dan hasrat mereka. TY mengatakan di sini "kali ini 2"sementara kita liat sungchan dan shotaro benar² menuruni tangga. ini mewakili 2 anggota lagi yang telah tersedot ke dalam gelombang otak bersama NCT tentang mimpi yg terhubung.
kemudian kita melihat TY dengan pasir dan kilatan jam pasir yang mewakili kehancuran waktu. Mengkonfirmasi bahwa kita sekarang berada di dunia mimpi.pada dasarnya shotaro menemukan "video" atau dunia 7th sense... kita bisa tahu dari dia menemukan lampu merah melalui celah di dinding. artinya shotaro mulai bermimpi menjadi anggota NCT setelah melihat MV 7th sense. sungchan meniru gerakan TY dengan peluit. Artinya sungchan bermimpi menjadi anggota NCT setelah melihat TY (dan ingin menjadi dia.... meniru tindakannya). tapi menariknya TY memiliki peluit dan dia adalah pemimpin 127 dan pemimpin dari  NCT...
pelatih tim olahraga juga memiliki peluit...
ini bisa menunjukkan bahwa sungchan akan menjadi pemimpin unit NCT yang akan datang nanti.

tambahan:Kilatan super cepat dari tumpukan layar tv/komputer... di NCTMENTARY yang mewakili gelombang otak para anggota dengan mereka di tumpuk satu sama lain mewakili koneksi gelombang otak mereka. disini kilatan cepat berarti, bahwa gelombang otak sungchan dan shotaro sekarang telah terhubung dengan yang lain.

Tambahan lagi: dari sini kita tahu dan ditunjukkan bahwa Anak kecil yang baju putih di SM_NCT # 1 : origin. Adalah Taeyong.

semoga ini bisa membantu...
video ini membuat gw merinding...
gw sangat menyarankan agar kalian menonton ulang NCTMENTARY.Orang dalam SM mengatakan bahwa era NCT UNIVERSE akan sangat bersangkutan dengan era Empati...
yaaa pada dasarnya ini adalah kelanjutan dari cerita/teori langsung dari era NCT Empati...,,,

author: @bini23bujank68
text:
Mksdnya bner gk sih  disini nunjukin kalau Sungchan sama Shotaro dapet the 7th sense yang bisa liat tentang the origin dulu.

The origin ini tuh video start adanya NCT. Anak kecil itu tuh Taeyong. Jadi ya bisa dibilang Taeyong know everything. Adanya unit baru juga Taeyong duluan yang bakal komunikasi sama Sungchan dan Shotaro. Karena dia awal mulanya NCT gitu pokoknya. Jadi everything start from Taeyong as a pilar atau anak kecil yang ada di video itu. Warna NCT tuh waktu di MV resonance juga sama kaya warna crayon yang dikasih si mbaknya ke anak kecil.

Kalau ditanya kenapa Sungchan bisa connect ke Taeyong? Kalau kata gue Sungchan kemungkinan besar leader ( masih dugaan ) makanya dia yang bisa komunikasi langsung. Kemungkinan kenapa Sungchan bisa niup terus TY denger. Antara SC mau sadarin TY atau Sungchan udah sadar mimpi dia itu buatan Taeyong terus dia mau nyoba komunikasi langsung sama Taeyong. Ini mah antara Sungchan yang datengin Taeyong atau Taeyong yang emang datengin Sungchan. Jadi disini diceritain kalau sungchan shotaro juga punya the 7th sense. Part mereka turun tangga itu artinya mereka masuk ke alam bawah sadar (mimpi), yang ngundang mereka adalah taeyong. Dan part sungchan yang nonton video nctmentary itu lagi cari tau kisah awalnya gimana, dari sini kemungkinan besar sungchan akan jadi leader di new unit.

Taeyong punya kuasa, dia yang bisa buka gerbang mimpi dan juga ngendaliin. Kenapa sungchan bawa peluit?? Menurutku karena dia akan jadi leader, peluit sebagai tanda undangan agar para member new unit berkumpul Dan buat shotaro, dia pas masuk alam bawah sadar berbeda ruangan sama sungchan. Disini shotaro denger suara peluit sungchan, tapi dia harus cari jalan keluar yang mengarah ke asal suara itu.

author: @angelmaymendoza8703
text:
(NOTE: LONG THEORY RECAP)
0:10 This sound is the same sound they used last NCT 2020, in the intro video https://youtu.be/U4zFN5RzPeM (which I heard first in 127's Neo Zone [Kick It] album intro) and it is right at the part wherein WayV shows up in the video after a mix of 127 and Dream

About the 2020 intro video - if you can all remember, it was when all the theories of 127 being the origin, dream being the place where they all "meet" or start out, and then WayV being the Vision wherein WayV members come from an alternate future - and in thethe video, Ten signals "Level 2" (new NCTzens: if you read the comments, you can see the theories in detail) - come together. 

The part wherein it switches between Taeyong and Sungchan's gazes - This all strengthens their original universe hints about *multiple "personalities"* that they (more specifically, Yuta who said it in Japanese) showed in NCT 2016 promo videos, Taeyong and Mark in their solo SuperM trailers(multiple Taeyongs clapping at a scene of TY shooting himself, white Mark climbing up and opening a box to black Mark rapping, even black Ten pulling white Ten into an empty canvas to transform it into a whole painting [and Lucas walking among many other Lucas but that's a reach already]), and probably throughout some Music Videos and lyrics (I'm forgetful so I probably can't remember everything rn lol)

And let's not forget the roles so far - Haechan was given the chronicler role probably because he was part of both units and can record everything, right? Now dreams are where they meet - and most dreamies were talking about meeting in their dreams (which at the time I interpreted as either everyone meeting in U, or meeting in Dreams because one day they would separate) then Mark suddenly says they were inside Ten's dream - and if Ten probably didn't have a hiatus right after debuting due to the knee injury, I think they would've visited this role more since he had the solo Dream in a Dream - so Ten is the Dreamer, and we have the Sticker (Jaehyun? idek), and I can't remember anymore. And Taeyong is the center of everything (idek anymore lol they should've given him the Sticker role since it fits if it means stick)

I wonder how they will add another unit into the storyline. I like WayV's by far, since it hasn't changed (NCT Dream is now a fixed unit and 127 isn't truly limitless anymore, I hope, since NCT U is limitless now) WayV's promo has turned global instead of targeted solely at China, but their concept hasn't changed - they're like the 127 superhero versions from the future, with NCT Dream's opposite vibes as the Nightmare, since they are trying to return to the past. Probably some alternate Dystopian universe. AND don't forget Ten being the Dreamer - his solo Dream in a Dream with Lucas ft for the first time, plus his solo New Heroes just strengthens my superhero trying to travel back in time theory lol. And let's be honest their concepts from debut til now invokes SO many theories. I just hope the new group will have a great concept as well, something they've already thought of before NCT even debuted hopefully so the story doesn't feel messed up. I wouldn't mind not arriving in Kwangya for the next few NCT years since this has so much potential (I just reaaally hope Kwangya wasn't just referring to Aespa and SM's new building lol it makes no sense to send Ten and Yangyang first if it's just the damn building like what one Czennie said lol)

I know I'm not mentioning everything and I'm missing a lot of key points but my memory sucks. Laksjdhfg

And also that one comment talking about 2021 escalator being the letter N, 2020 being the letter C, and 2018 being the letter T, all showing that yes T7s so we're all back in tune, y'all that is just amazing

Well, it's been a long ass ride. NCT 2021 Let's go

author: @tcole750
text:
VIDEO EXPLANATION:

For those that don’t understand… this video is takes us back to the NCTmentary during Empathy Era. Basically NCT is based on the idea of the members being connected through sharing the same dream. The NCTmentary talks about the members sharing the same brainwaves and connecting their hopes and passions. The title of the video “The 1st Encounter” is Sungchan and Shotaro’s 1st experience with dreaming about NCT or dreaming about becoming NCT. TY senses them coming into NCT’s shared dream and says “this time 2” while we see Sungchan and Shotaro literally descending stairs. This represents 2 more members that have been sucked into NCT’s shared brainwaves of connected dreams.

Then we see TY with the sand and flashes of an hourglass representing the destruction of time. Confirming that we are now in the dream world. Basically Shotaro comes across the 7th sense “video” or world.. we can tell by him discovering the red light through the crack in the wall. This means that Shotaro began to dream about becoming a NCT member after seeing the 7th Sense MV. Notice that Taro is watching behind a closed door.. remember that Taro used to be the biggest NCT fanboy making NCT dance cover videos on tiktok before getting scouted by SM. He was watching them at a distance as a fan or behind a closed door. 

Sungchan is mimicking TY’s actions with the whistle. Meaning that Sungchan dreamt of becoming a NCT member after seeing TY (and wanting to be like him… mimicking his actions). We know that Sungchan was a trainee with Jungwoo, so he’s not behind a closed door here. He was able to admire TY from a close distance. But interestingly TY has the whistle and he’s the leader of 127 and the leader of all of NCT… coaches of sport teams also have whistles… this could represent that Sungchan will be the leader of whatever new NCT unit he will be in later. Him blowing the whistle is him accepting he role as a leader. 

EDIT: the super quick flash of the pile of tv/computer screens… in the NCTMENTARY that represents the members brainwaves with them being piled on each other representing the connection of their brainwaves. Here the quick flash means that Sungchan and Shotaro’s brainwaves have now been connected with the others.

Hope this helps.. this video literally gave me goosebumps. I highly recommend you go back and watch the entire NCTMENTARY if you haven’t. A SM insider said that NCT Universe era will be heavily biased on Empathy.. it will basically be a continuation of Empathy.

author: @imjopping
text:
THERE'S SO MUCH TO DISSECT!!  SungTaro watching the original concept trailer, Taeyong with the sands (of time, from the hour glass and the beach from the original trailer, and now I'm even more curious about the very obvious moment in Analog Trip where Taeyong mentioned the giant hourglass on the wall), The 7th Sense music and lighting just at the whistle (we've been getting a lot of whistles/flutes lately huh NCTzens? It can't be a coincidence then!) and then the T7S red hits, but now with the strip of light across their eyes like in the New Axis teaser pics!  So somehow they combine/relate!  And a new axis on the spatial grid of reality is, what, consciousness still?  Time and 3 spatial locations, what is the new axis going to be?  

Excerpt from the wiki page for Coordinate Time: 
In the theory of relativity, it is convenient to express results in terms of a spacetime coordinate system relative to an implied observer. In many (but not all) coordinate systems, an event is specified by one time coordinate and three spatial coordinates. The time specified by the time coordinate is referred to as coordinate time to distinguish it from proper time.

In the special case of an inertial observer in special relativity, by convention the coordinate time at an event is the same as the proper time measured by a clock that is at the same location as the event, that is stationary relative to the observer and that has been synchronised to the observer's clock using the Einstein synchronisation convention.

author: @yawnz3960
text:
My very confusing theory...

"this time, two" taeyong somehow guessed how many new members were coming(?), he might be like a guardian or like a time-keeper(hourglass) who watches over them(NCT) and lead them to this world(Universe) and show them what the world is like. Both sungchan and taeyong have the whistle, sungchan blew on it and somehow discovered a way into the world(?), while when shotaro touched the wall(probably the earlier members also went into from), this somehow showed him what the first(earliest) world of the "Universe" looked like when it was found(probably by that "person" on the on the beach/desert, it might be young taeyong). Since this is called "The 7th sense (The first encounter of a Dream)" it might mean that sungchan and shotaro found this for the first time and just like the other members they also entered this "Dream" (when shotaro touched the wall he also saw a bit part of when the earlier member entered the dream). text: 오밤중에 nctmentary 다시 봄.....ㅋㅋㅋㅋ 성찬이랑 타로가 등장하는 연출이 쿤이 묘사한 몽중몽 단계 진입이랑 똑같음. 쿤이 깊은 원형계단을 타고 내려가서 빛이 새어나오는 문을 열고 들어갔더니 비현실적으로 멋진공간이 나왔고 문득 깨달았다고 함. 아 이거 몽중몽이구나. 애들이  저 붉은 빛 나는 공간으로  들어가진 않았지만, 성찬이가 피리를 분 이후에 태용과 함께 타로 성찬이 붉은 조명을 맞았으므로, 태용이로 대표되는 다른 nct들과 같은 단계의 몽중몽에 진입했단 얘기같고. 몽중몽은 꿈이 현실이고 현실이 꿈이 되는 곳이고 몽중몽에서 애들은 잃어버린 현실의 조각을 맞추면 그것은 곧 현실이 된다고 했다. 레조넌스에서 공명으로 서로를 완전히 인식하고 공유했으니 아마 이번 앨범에서 꿈이 현실이 되어 뭔가 새로운 현실로 간 애들을 보여줄 것 같음. "우주보다 더 넓고 깊은 꿈을 통해 만난 우리들. 더이상 현실의 한계에 부딪히지 않고 바람보다 가볍게 날아오른다. 드림랩은 꿈을 현실화 하기 위해 만들어졌다." 앨범제목 유니버스하고도 연결할 수 있을것 같고..., 이번 앨범에서 애들 꿈 세계관( 이상을 현실에 실현하기 위해 꿈을 꿨던 것들)이 1차적으로 마무리 될것 같은 느낌적 느낌

author: @notyoutubechannel
text:
I think I clearly get what this video all about. SungTaro haven't introduced yet properly (like having their own units). So maybe SM will debut a new unit or maybe  a duo? (i don't know really). They use The 7th Sense because they have two new members having the same dream and the song The 7th Sense is the one connects them (in terms of music and dream). If you'll look up to the lyrics of The 7th Sense there's a line saying "Gateun kkum machi nal bureuneun
Iksukhan norae machimnae yeongyeoldwae" or in English "In the same dream I hear a familiar
Song that calls to me, it connects us" like probably every new members calling is the song The 7th Sense. You'll notice that Shotaro already hears something from the other side and when he opened the door The 7th Sense was played. So maybe they are hinting us that this comeback SungTaro will have their respective units.
